title: Rb and Cs isotopic distributions from 1-GeV proton fission of U-238.

x4freetext: Rb and Cs isotopic distributions from 1-GeV proton
fission of U-238.

x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.348, p.479 (1980)

flag.help: Reference to related data compiled in another entry

x4freetext: The data were
used for normalization of authors` data.
Last checking has been done.
The uranium target made of a combination of 30 thin
graphite plates, 0.08 mm in thickness, with a deposited
1.5 mg/cm**2 layer of uranium carbide.
.Deduced nucleon losses.
An electron multiplier with a noise level lower than
1 pulse/S was used as detector. Mass spectra of Rb and
Cs ions were registrated by means of an electrostatic
sweep-generator and multi-channel analyzer synchronized
with the proton bunch of the accelerator.

x4codes.hlp: On-line mass separation of a product

x4freetext: A two-stage mass spectrometer on-line.
*By authors* the corrections for isobar and isotope
decay during the extraction time were taken into
account, as well as the variation in the diffusion
coefficient due to additional heating of the target by
the proton beam.

Low limit of uncertainty of absolute value.
